metadata.description:
The painter climbed the stairs to his dilapidated workshop. 
He did not see well where he stepped, it had been a hard day of cirrhosis and smoke in his eyes. 
Right on the bottom rung, he let his foot slip, tripped, and hit his head violently on the floor. 

Then, it began one of his most lucid journeys.

metadata.name: Ersbla #256
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: Slanted #115
metadata.description:
Fun little game, simple rules:
- start with a randomly sized grid
- pick 2 random cells
- recursively, every cell draw itself
- then it picks two of its neighbors for the next step

Some cells are drawn multiple times, some others are never picked up, but the process it's not completely random.

metadata.name: Celebration in Times of Measure #48
metadata.description:
Intentionally developed by placing constraints on the process.

Everything is generated by code written in P5js.

Press '1' for the default, textured version
Press '2' to add outlines and see the form structure

Press '3' to see a flat, untextured version
Press '4' to add outlines (flat version)

Press 'e' to end/skip the initial animation
Press 'r' to restart/replay the animation
Press 's' to save current image (in live view)

Created by Walter Anderson (@noxiarb)

metadata.name: Garden of Imagination #9
metadata.description:
The more a garden can sharpen all senses, the better.

The garden is one of the most artistic expressions where the five human senses are explored (sight, smell, sound, taste and touch).
It's very good to be impressed by many different colors and shapes, feel the perfume of flowers, feel the textures of plants, taste the fruits and hear the noise of leaves and birds. The more a garden manages to sharpen all the senses, the better it fulfills its role.
The challenge of this project is to provide as many sensations as possible, some you will get visually and others you will need imagination. Imagination is an essential part of this project. There are different species from different cultures that, after becoming relatives, start to interact with each other.

The Garden of Imagination is layered artwork generated from a pool of previously rendered digital assets developed for several months.

- Use the "S" key to export an image.
